  "previous_mistake_explained": {
    "what_i_did_wrong": "I treated 'INDEXING_ALLOWED' as if it meant 'not indexed yet.' This was incorrect.",
    "what_indexing_allowed_actually_means": "INDEXING_ALLOWED means Google's systems have determined the page is eligible for indexing. It is the NORMAL, expected state for pages that ARE in the index. It means 'no robots block, no noindex, Google permits this page to be indexed.' It does NOT mean the page is pending or waiting.",
    "what_coverage_state_means": "coverageState is the human-readable GSC report label. 'Submitted and indexed' is the highest-confidence signal from GSC that a page IS in the index. This field should be treated as authoritative for index presence.",
    "why_both_fields_together_mean_indexed": "coverageState='Submitted and indexed' (GSC says it's in the indexed bucket) + indexingState='INDEXING_ALLOWED' (no technical block) + verdict=PASS (healthy page) + canonical match = CONFIRMED INDEXED"
  },

